  "prompt": "Can I download and listen to music in offline mode on the Spotify app on Volvo Sensus?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Spotify does allow offline listening, but this feature is primarily available on mobile devices like smartphones and tablets with a Spotify Premium account. While you can stream Spotify through the Volvo Sensus infotainment system, the offline mode for downloading songs might not be supported directly on the car's system.\n\nIf you're looking to listen to music offline while in your Volvo, you might consider downloading songs on your smartphone via the Spotify app and then connecting your phone to the car via Bluetooth or USB. This way, you can play your downloaded songs through the car's audio system.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, please check the official Spotify website or the Volvo Sensus manual.",
